The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • ROBERT D CAMPBELL was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • ROBERT D CAMPBELL was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:28 PM Defendant ROBERT D CAMPBELL in court.  Attorney Nils Wyosnick in court for ROBERT D CAMPBELL.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 with probation and count 2 with jail, fine, costs, DL revocation, IID and AODA and count 3 will be dismissed. ADA concurs. Atty Wyosnick concurs. Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant. Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights. Court goes over the elements of each offense. Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty. Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions. 

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY. Court finds the plea is made knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court finds the defendant guilty as charged on counts 1 & 2 and orders count 3 be dismissed outright. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today. Sentencing statement by ADA. Sentencing statement by Atty Wyosnick. Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

COUNT 1

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 3 years.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs. To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office.  Monies are to be paid during the first year of probation.  Failure to pay may result in the suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  You may be randomly tested for compliance. 
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment and follow-up as recommended. 
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 

COUNT 2 (OWI - 2nd)

-100 days county jail. Sentence is to commence within 60 days.  Court grants huber, out-of-county service and out-of-county travel. 
-$500 fine plus costs. Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or call the Clerk of Courts Office (920-294-4142) to set-up a payment plan. 
-DL revocation - 15 months
-IID - 15 months
-AODA (GL)
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 

Court grants the defendant 18 days of sentence credit on the OWI.
